{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"515ab1ef-0037-4acd-82c9-4b45010edbb1","content":"In MSTest 3.x, `TestContext` is injected via the constructor, and you can use `[ClassInitialize]`/`[TestInitialize]` for sync setup or implement `IAsyncInitialization` — but the simplest async pattern uses the built-in lifecycle attributes.\n\nHere's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // One-time async setup for the class\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassSetup(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // Expensive shared setup (DB, service clients, etc.)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Per-test async setup\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task TestSetup()\n    {\n        // Runs before each test; can use _testContext here\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Per-test async teardown\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task TestTeardown()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // One-time async teardown for the class\n    [ClassCleanup]\n    public static async Task ClassTeardown()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points (MSTest 3.x):**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is passed via the constructor; no need for the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern.\n- **Async lifecycle** — `[ClassInitialize]`, `[TestInitialize]`, `[TestCleanup]`, and `[ClassCleanup]` all support `async Task` signatures.\n- **Execution order**: Constructor → `ClassInitialize` (once) → `TestInitialize` → Test → `TestCleanup` → … → `ClassCleanup`.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a test file in your project with this pattern?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b9a4adfa-1586-4a2d-bc99-bf15347f9989","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project uses MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), `TestContext` can be injected via constructor. Let me provide the recommended pattern.","outputTokens":608,"requestId":"802B:28B2DA:174B767:18AB401:6A046100"},"id":"c715aacc-d08a-4c59-9fa5-3a696bc80b2f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:31:27.753Z","parentId":"70ab4ff5-b87b-4c12-92db-6cfe279802ea"}
